C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Hbl\acuexpacu\HblAcu\Hbl.c
      1          /**
      2           *  @file       
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      HBL - Hardware Base Line
      5           *
      6           *  @details    This module implements the generic handler for Hbl for ACU profiles where it handles LOADS, PILOTS, GIs and LLIs
      7           *              Features that can be configured as ENABLED/DISABLED in Hbl_prv.h:
      8           *              HBL_USES_EXPANSION_GIS                  - Enable use of API012Exp to handle Expansion GIs
      9           *              HBL_CROSS_LOADS_FEATURE                 - Enable Cross Load Feature - handled by CrossLoads module
     10           *              HBL_XLOAD_MASTER_RELAY_SUPPORT          - Enable Master Relay Cross Load feature - HBL_CROSS_LOADS_FEATURE should be ENABLED
     11           *              HBL_XLOAD_SWITCH_RELAY_SUPPORT          - Enable Master Relay Cross Load feature - HBL_CROSS_LOADS_FEATURE should be ENABLED
     12           *              HBL_XLOAD_REVERSE_SWITCH_RELAY_SUPPORT  - Enable Master Relay Cross Load feature - HBL_CROSS_LOADS_FEATURE should be ENABLED
     13           *              HBL_XLOAD_TRANSITION_RELAY_SUPPORT      - Enable Master Relay Cross Load feature - HBL_CROSS_LOADS_FEATURE should be ENABLED
     14           *              HBL_LOADS_QUEUE_FEATURE                 - Enable Loads Queue feature to get commands from Api005 and queue in SRHbl__Process()
     15           *              HBL_LOADS_QUEUE_CALLED_FROM_HBL         - (ENABLED by default) Perform all queue commands into Hbl module
     16           *              HBL_USE_DIRECT_LOAD_OVERRIDE            - (ENABLED by default) Allows Direct Load configuration using HBL_DIRECT_LOAD[] array;
     17           *                                                          Load ID listed there will be forced as Direct Loads; those not listed there
     18           *                                                          and with no Load Handler should not have Load Parameters to be configured as Direct Loads.
     19           *              HBL_KEEP_LOADS_OFF_FEATURE              - (DISABLED by default) Feature to set Loads requests OFF when a fast reaction is required,
     20           *                                                          e.g. a Brownout condition has been detected.
     21           *              HBL_KEEP_LOADS_OFF_PRIORITY             - Priority level to consider for Keep Loads OFF: all loads set with a priority lower than it will be forced OFF.
     22           *                                                          Default is minimum Class B (SRHBL_PRIORITY_CLASSB_LO)
     23           *                                                          If it set higher, it will be limited to minimum Class B value anyway.
     24           *              HBL_KEEP_LOADS_OFF_EXCLUDE_FEATURE      - (DISABLED by default) Allows to set a list of load ID to exclude from Keep Loads Off action at all.
     25           *              HBL_KEEP_LOADS_OFF_EXCLUDE_LIST_DEF     - Comma separated list of HBL Load ID to skip keep OFF process, regardless of Priority.
     26           *                                                          If not defined, all loads will be turned OFF.
     27           *              HBLACU__EXTINT_CALLBACK(channel)        - HANDLE WITH CARE! (Blank - no function called by default.) It allows to configure an ExtIntHandler
     28           *                                                          callback for ExtInterrupt events enabled but not related to ZeroCross - ZeroCross pin
     29           *                                                          will not call this function.
     30           *                                                          "channel" is the ExtInt channel that generated interrupt.
     31           *
     32           *	@defgroup	CLASS_B
     33           *
     34           *  @copyright  Copyright 2015 Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     35           */
